@page "/dashboard/docs/decision-guides"

<div class="page-head"><h2>Choosing a model</h2></div>

<DocsPage Slug="decision-guides">
    <h1>Choosing a networking model</h1>
    <p class="lead">Pick the SpawnWeaver features that fit your game — and know what isn't a fit yet.</p>

    <h2>By game type</h2>
    <table>
        <thead><tr><th>I'm building…</th><th>Use</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr><td>A turn-based game</td><td>Room state + persistence</td></tr>
            <tr><td>A casual co-op game</td><td>Rooms + entity state + events</td></tr>
            <tr><td>A lobby/party game</td><td>Lobbies + ready checks + rooms</td></tr>
            <tr><td>A top-down 1v1 / small arena</td><td>Matchmaking + rooms + entity state (interpolate on the client)</td></tr>
            <tr><td>A persistent-progression game</td><td>Persistence + rooms</td></tr>
            <tr><td>A competitive shooter</td><td>Needs dedicated authoritative servers — the relay/state sync isn't enough</td></tr>
            <tr><td>An MMO</td><td>Not supported yet</td></tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2>Great for</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Indie &amp; small-team games</li>
        <li>Lobbies, matchmaking, party games</li>
        <li>Casual co-op &amp; turn-based</li>
        <li>Lightweight realtime games (with client-side interpolation)</li>
        <li>Player profiles, progression, and inventory persistence</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Not yet for</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Competitive shooters that need server-authoritative simulation</li>
        <li>Full MMOs and large-world replication</li>
        <li>Server-authoritative physics, rollback netcode, lag compensation</li>
        <li>Advanced anti-cheat, voice chat</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
        State sync v1 is a simple, broadcast-based layer — it keeps players aligned but does not
        prevent a determined cheat from sending false state. For competitive integrity you need an
        authoritative server, which is outside SpawnWeaver's current scope.
    </p>

